programme.title: Flog It ! S13
programme.desc: This edition comes from the historic Blackpool Tower Circus, where presenter Paul Martin is joined by experts Anita Manning and James Lewis. Together the team pick out a selection of interesting antiques and collectables to be sold at a local auction. James discovers some terracotta tomb figures that could be over a thousand years old, and Anita gets her hands on a collection of seaside postcards. But the real star of the show is a well-preserved concertina. Paul also takes a look around one of Lancashire's most famous theatres, the Morecambe Winter Gardens, where he follows in the footsteps of Laurence Olivier and Laurel and Hardy.

programme.title: Scotland v Wales
programme.desc: Live coverage from Edinburgh, where Scotland host Wales in the second weekend of the Women's Six Nations. Wales came from 19-7 down to win 24-19 last year - it was their second win of the 2022 championship, and they went on to finish third behind Grand Slam winners England and France. For Scotland, it was the second of what would prove to be five defeats in a campaign that saw them end up with the wooden spoon. The Scots will be determined to avoid that fate in 2023 but can take hope from the fact that the last time they hosted France, in the Six Nations in 2021, they won 27-20.
